      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BUNKER HUT (1) raced up on the speed and looked a chance only to be edged out in a very busy finish first-up over 1300m at Randwick. Beaten narrowly second-up last prep in a BM94 over this distance at Rosehill. Loves Kembla and is the one they have to beat. CHARCOALS (3) went back from a wide draw before making substantial late ground to finish fifth when fresh from a spell over this trip at Randwick last time out. Has won two from three when second-up and four from six at 1200m - those are the right credentials. MONTE KATE (7) has raced on the pace and saluted at her last two outings, both over 1250m at Canterbury. Three-time winner here, including twice at this journey. Big chance with just 53.5kgs after the claim. WELL TIMED (2) did nothing first-up but added fitness and blinkers may spark something extra. LULUMON (8) is fitter for two runs back from a spell and should play a role in the outcome.",
